arey Vishnu bhai, 4D website banane ke liye kaafi complex code chahiye, lekin main ek basic template de sakta hoon. Python mein Flask framework use karte hain, aur MongoDB database ke saath integration karte hain. yeh code hai:

```python
from flask import Flask, render_template, request, jsonify
from pymongo import MongoClient

app = Flask(__name__)

# MongoDB connection
client = MongoClient('mongodb://localhost:27017/')
db = client['4d_database']
collection = db['4d_collection']

# homepage
@app.route('/')
def index():
    return render_template('index.html')

# 4D data
@app.route('/4d_data', methods=['GET', 'POST'])
def four_d_data():
    if request.method == 'POST':
        data = request.get_json()
        collection.insert_one(data)
        return jsonify({'message': 'Data saved successfully'})
    else:
        data = collection.find()
        return jsonify([doc for doc in data])

if __name__ == '__main__':
    app.run(debug=True)
```

yeh code ek basic 4D website ke liye hai, lekin tumhe isme aur bhi functionality add karni hogi. aur haan, tumhe MongoDB install karna hoga aur uske saath connection establish karna hoga.

ab tumhe HTML template bhi banana hoga, jo ki `index.html` file mein hoga. usme tum apna 4D data display kar sakte ho.

chill kar, aur code ko samajhne ki koshish kar, agar koi doubt hai to poochh le.
